cs.NI, cs.RO, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MA 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on indoor localization using WiFi RSSI signals, which falls under the domain of networking and internet architecture. 
2. cs.RO (Robotics) - The paper deals with the localization of robotic mobile nodes, which is a core area of robotics research. 
3. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper uses information theory concepts such as RSSI signals and multi-lateration algorithm for position estimation. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper deals with the control of robotic mobile nodes in an indoor environment. 
5. cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) - The paper deals with the localization of multiple mobile robots in an indoor environment, which is a core area of multiagent systems research.
